WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:02:21.268 --> 00:02:23.770
House Velaryon is coming for you!

3
00:02:24.438 --> 00:02:27.441
The Sea Snake will have
your poxy fucking head!

4
00:02:28.066 --> 00:02:30.485
No. no. no. No. please!

5
00:02:37.409 --> 00:02:39.995
Fuck you. Prince Drahar!

6
00:02:40.078 --> 00:02:43.540
Fuck your whore mother
and bastard father!

7
00:02:46.001 --> 00:02:48.628
No. no! No!

8
00:03:12.819 --> 00:03:14.071
Dragon!

9
00:03:14.154 --> 00:03:17.366
Hail Prince Daemon!

10
00:03:19.826 --> 00:03:22.996
Burn the fucking Triarchy cunts alive!

11
00:03:30.712 --> 00:03:32.130
Here. my Prince.

12
00:03:33.298 --> 00:03:35.050
Save me!

13
00:03:43.642 --> 00:03:45.102
To the caves! Now!

14
00:03:53.276 --> 00:03:54.986
Retreat to the caves!

15
00:04:17.884 --> 00:04:19.261
Where are you?

16
00:04:21.680 --> 00:04:23.890
Come out and face me. Drahar!

17
00:04:25.976 --> 00:04:28.228
Come out. Drahar!

18
00:04:28.728 --> 00:04:30.439
Where are you?

19
00:04:31.481 --> 00:04:33.984
I'm gonna feed you to your own crabs!

20
00:04:34.776 --> 00:04:36.278
Where are you?

21
00:05:14.316 --> 00:05:15.796
He has your hair. Your Grace.

22
00:05:17.027 --> 00:05:18.528
He does have my hair.

23
00:05:18.612 --> 00:05:21.072
- He has your eyes. Your Grace.
- Yes. he does.

24
00:05:23.158 --> 00:05:24.635
And you have my nose.
don't you?

25
00:05:24.659 --> 00:05:28.830
Two years old and already our boy
has a kingly presence.

26
00:05:29.331 --> 00:05:32.167
He may yet. brother.
but this morning he insisted on eating

27
00:05:32.250 --> 00:05:33.960
porridge with his hands.

28
00:05:35.587 --> 00:05:36.880
He will grow.

29
00:05:38.215 --> 00:05:41.051
We're quite a party
assembled in his honor.

30
00:05:42.010 --> 00:05:45.472
And surely by the end of this hunt.
we shall have more to celebrate.

31
00:05:45.555 --> 00:05:47.682
And what is that. pray tell.

32
00:05:47.766 --> 00:05:49.935
It is Aegon's second name day.

33
00:05:50.018 --> 00:05:51.436
His infancy's behind him.

34
00:05:51.937 --> 00:05:54.564
It only remains for Viserys to name him
heir to the throne.

35
00:05:54.648 --> 00:05:56.900
I wouldn't be so sure.

36
00:05:56.983 --> 00:05:58.485
He's the King's firstborn son.

37
00:05:58.568 --> 00:06:01.446
I don't know that His Grace
sees it so clearly.

38
00:06:03.114 --> 00:06:05.742
Then it lies with you
to make him see it...

39
00:06:06.493 --> 00:06:08.328
Lord Hand.

40
00:06:08.411 --> 00:06:09.829
Your Grace...

41
00:06:11.748 --> 00:06:13.959
I bring urgent news from the Stepstones.

42
00:06:14.626 --> 00:06:16.962
The Crabfeeder has dug in
for siege on Bloodstone

43
00:06:17.045 --> 00:06:19.506
while his men sabotage our fleet
under the cover of dark.

44
00:06:19.589 --> 00:06:20.966
Not today. Tyland.

45
00:06:21.049 --> 00:06:24.177
The matter of the Stepstones
is regrettably urgent.

46
00:06:24.261 --> 00:06:25.971
It's been three years.

47
00:06:26.054 --> 00:06:28.306
It can wait another three days.

48
00:06:32.477 --> 00:06:34.563
Come. eat.

49
00:06:34.646 --> 00:06:36.898
Fortify yourselves for the journey.

50
00:06:38.066 --> 00:06:39.192
Please.

51
00:06:39.901 --> 00:06:41.278
Is the baggage train ready?

52
00:06:41.361 --> 00:06:43.488
It is presently massing
at the River Gate.

53
00:06:43.572 --> 00:06:46.324
Lord Jason expects us
in the Kingswood before midday.

54
00:06:46.408 --> 00:06:49.703
- Have you seen Rhaenyra?
- I have not. Your Grace.

55
00:06:51.788 --> 00:06:55.083
With the Triarchy now sheltering
in Bloodstone's caves.

56
00:06:55.166 --> 00:06:57.586
the threat of the dragons is blunted.

57
00:06:57.669 --> 00:06:59.713
They don't have foot soldiers.

58
00:06:59.796 --> 00:07:03.174
But their sellswords have been
withdrawing in droves. Your Grace.

59
00:07:03.258 --> 00:07:06.469
Even the mercenaries can see
that it is a losing effort.

60
00:07:06.553 --> 00:07:07.637
Where's Rhaenyra?

61
00:07:08.179 --> 00:07:09.806
I cannot be sure at present. Your Grace.

62
00:07:09.889 --> 00:07:12.976
The Velaryon forces have suffered
heavy attrition. Your Grace.

63
00:07:13.852 --> 00:07:16.563
The seeds of dissent are sown
amongst the rank and file.

64
00:07:17.314 --> 00:07:19.357
Daemon has driven the men hard.

65
00:07:19.441 --> 00:07:21.901
They have begun to question his command.

66
00:07:22.902 --> 00:07:25.488
If the Crown were ever to intervene...

67
00:07:25.572 --> 00:07:26.799
- Tyland...
- ...now is the time.

68
00:07:26.823 --> 00:07:29.159
Daemon and the Sea Snake
started their war

69
00:07:29.242 --> 00:07:31.286
without His Grace's leave.

70
00:07:31.369 --> 00:07:34.080
Were he to intervene now after so long.

71
00:07:34.164 --> 00:07:35.999
it would make the Crown appear weak.

72
00:07:36.082 --> 00:07:37.584
Can someone tell me

73
00:07:37.667 --> 00:07:40.587
where in the seven hells
Rhaenyra might be?

74
00:07:40.670 --> 00:07:45.759
<i>Under the dragon's eye</i>

75
00:07:46.885 --> 00:07:52.057
<i>Under the dragon's eye</i>

76
00:07:52.599 --> 00:07:53.683
Again.

77
00:07:55.060 --> 00:07:57.270
Perhaps the Princess
might like to hear something else?

78
00:07:57.354 --> 00:07:59.189
She would not. Play it again.

79
00:08:05.236 --> 00:08:08.281
<i>She fled with her ships</i>

80
00:08:08.365 --> 00:08:11.201
<i>And her people</i>

81
00:08:11.284 --> 00:08:14.454
<i>Her heart broken for those...</i>

82
00:08:15.455 --> 00:08:16.790
Your Grace.

83
00:08:16.873 --> 00:08:18.249
Did I say to stop?

84
00:08:22.629 --> 00:08:24.839
From the beginning.

85
00:08:30.470 --> 00:08:33.474
<i>She fled with her ships</i>

86
00:08:33.556 --> 00:08:36.476
- Rhaenyra?
- Yes. my queen?

87
00:08:37.185 --> 00:08:39.479
Your presence is wanted
in the outer courtyard.

88
00:08:39.562 --> 00:08:41.731
The royal hunt readies to depart.

89
00:08:41.815 --> 00:08:44.693
I've decided to remain here
and read instead.

90
00:08:46.736 --> 00:08:48.154
You may go. Samwell.

91
00:08:48.905 --> 00:08:51.282
You are to stay
by order of the Princess.

92
00:08:51.991 --> 00:08:55.161
The Queen commands you
to leave the Godswood at once.

93
00:08:57.580 --> 00:08:58.790
Princess.

94
00:09:01.918 --> 00:09:03.002
Your Grace.

95
00:09:06.715 --> 00:09:08.475
The King wishes
for you to join us.

96
00:09:08.550 --> 00:09:11.344
The King has much to celebrate.
He does not need me.

97
00:09:11.428 --> 00:09:13.188
He wants for us all
to be together.

98
00:09:14.055 --> 00:09:17.058
Perhaps the hunt could be... fun.

99
00:09:18.226 --> 00:09:19.978
Is it the King's command?

100
00:09:21.020 --> 00:09:23.231
- Yes. but it...
- Then at once. Your Grace.

101
00:09:24.149 --> 00:09:25.358
But it needn't be.

102
00:09:26.317 --> 00:09:29.738
None of it needs be this way
in truth. Rhaenyra.

103
00:09:38.538 --> 00:09:40.498
Well. isn't this splendid?

104
00:09:40.957 --> 00:09:42.959
The whole of our family
off to celebration

105
00:09:43.042 --> 00:09:44.961
and adventure in the Kingswood.

106
00:09:51.760 --> 00:09:53.803
Should you be traveling
in such condition?

107
00:09:53.887 --> 00:09:56.681
The maester said that being out
in nature would do me well.

108
00:09:57.182 --> 00:10:00.393
Well. you will be with your own child
sooner than late.

109
00:10:00.477 --> 00:10:02.520
and make me a proud grandsire.

110
00:10:04.189 --> 00:10:06.274
It's not so bad.

111
00:10:06.357 --> 00:10:09.778
The days are long. but Aegon
came quickly and without fuss.

112
00:10:17.702 --> 00:10:19.913
You should ride out with me today.

113
00:10:20.872 --> 00:10:21.956
Join in the chase.

114
00:10:22.832 --> 00:10:24.042
I'd rather not.

115
00:10:24.793 --> 00:10:27.962
The boars squeal like children
when they're being slaughtered.

116
00:10:28.046 --> 00:10:30.340
I find it discomforting.

117
00:10:30.423 --> 00:10:32.091
It's a hunt. Rhaenyra.

118
00:10:34.719 --> 00:10:37.472
How would you
like to participate?

119
00:10:37.555 --> 00:10:38.848
I'm not sure why I must.

120
00:10:38.932 --> 00:10:41.017
Because you are my daughter...

121
00:10:41.100 --> 00:10:42.185
The Princess.

122
00:10:43.228 --> 00:10:44.896
And you have duties.

123
00:10:44.979 --> 00:10:46.981
As I am ceaselessly reminded.

124
00:10:47.065 --> 00:10:49.359
- I'm sorry?
- As I am ceaselessly reminded.

125
00:10:49.442 --> 00:10:52.654
You wouldn't need to be reminded
if you ever attended to them.

126
00:10:52.737 --> 00:10:54.739
No one's here for me.

127
00:11:56.718 --> 00:11:59.762
Hail. hail Aegon. the Conqueror-Babe.
Second of His Name!

128
00:12:00.847 --> 00:12:03.600
Here's to His Grace
on his second name day!

129
00:12:50.104 --> 00:12:53.066
Lady Johanna was reported
to have been abducted

130
00:12:53.149 --> 00:12:56.277
when one of Lord Swann's ships
sailed through the Stepstones.

131
00:12:56.361 --> 00:12:58.071
What will happen to Lady Johanna?

132
00:12:58.154 --> 00:13:00.990
She's to be sold to a pillow house
in the Free Cities

133
00:13:01.074 --> 00:13:03.076
if you believe the rumors.

134
00:13:04.535 --> 00:13:07.163
I fear the gods did not
make me for hunting.

135
00:13:07.246 --> 00:13:08.665
Might I sit with you. my ladies?

136
00:13:08.748 --> 00:13:10.541
But of course. Please join us.

137
00:13:11.417 --> 00:13:14.921
Larys Strong. the youngest son of our
Master of Law. Lord Lyonel.

138
00:13:15.004 --> 00:13:16.547
My lord husband says that no king

139
00:13:16.631 --> 00:13:19.217
has even been able to tame
the Stepstones for long.

140
00:13:19.300 --> 00:13:22.345
It's an inhospitable place
suited only for savages.

141
00:13:22.428 --> 00:13:26.057
Perhaps the Princess...
can give us some insight.

142
00:13:26.849 --> 00:13:30.645
Oh. I'm not sure how I could.
I've never been to the Stepstones.

143
00:13:30.728 --> 00:13:33.731
Your dear uncle is the great mind
behind this war.

144
00:13:33.815 --> 00:13:35.692
- Is he not?
- I wouldn't know.

145
00:13:35.775 --> 00:13:37.193
I've not spoken to Daemon in years.

146
00:13:37.276 --> 00:13:39.195
Since you supplanted him as heir.

147
00:13:39.278 --> 00:13:41.447
Daemon made his choices. Lady Ceira.

148
00:13:42.115 --> 00:13:43.825
The Princess was more suited
to the role.

149
00:13:44.993 --> 00:13:47.996
He's made a mess
and the King must put an end to it.

150
00:13:48.079 --> 00:13:52.250
Send fleets and men
and clear out the Triarchy for good.

151
00:13:53.459 --> 00:13:55.086
But the Crown is not at war.

152
00:13:55.837 --> 00:13:58.923
The Crown... is at war. Princess.

153
00:13:59.007 --> 00:14:00.758
Though your father refuses to admit it.

154
00:14:00.842 --> 00:14:03.678
we've been dragged into it by your uncle
and the Sea Snake.

155
00:14:03.761 --> 00:14:07.306
And how have you served the realm
of late. Lady Redwyne. by eating cake?

156
00:14:40.423 --> 00:14:42.508
I wonder. Princess...

157
00:14:42.592 --> 00:14:45.219
was your own second name day
as grand as this?

158
00:14:45.887 --> 00:14:48.723
I honestly don't recall
and neither will Aegon.

159
00:14:51.350 --> 00:14:52.685
Lord Jason Lannister.

160
00:14:53.853 --> 00:14:56.105
I gathered that from all the lions.

161
00:14:56.189 --> 00:14:58.191
I don't think we've been
properly introduced.

162
00:15:01.277 --> 00:15:04.280
Your twin serves on my father's council.

163
00:15:04.781 --> 00:15:07.200
Tyland is...

164
00:15:07.283 --> 00:15:10.495
frightfully dull. gods love him.

165
00:15:10.578 --> 00:15:12.371
The finest honeyed wine
you'll ever taste.

166
00:15:12.455 --> 00:15:15.083
- Made in Lannisport. of course.
- Of course.

167
00:15:16.793 --> 00:15:19.879
The Kingswood.
it's fine hunting ground.

168
00:15:19.962 --> 00:15:22.423
But the best spot is to be
found at Casterly Rock.

169
00:15:22.507 --> 00:15:24.258
near my home.

170
00:15:24.342 --> 00:15:25.635
Have you been?

171
00:15:25.718 --> 00:15:27.804
Um. once... on tour

172
00:15:27.887 --> 00:15:29.514
with my mother when I was young.

173
00:15:29.597 --> 00:15:32.225
and honestly can't recall
much of that either.

174
00:15:32.308 --> 00:15:35.108
The Rock is thrice
the height of the Hightower in Oldtown.

175
00:15:35.186 --> 00:15:37.146
taller still than the Wall in the North.

176
00:15:37.230 --> 00:15:38.606
It's been said that

177
00:15:38.689 --> 00:15:42.068
if one were to stand in the tower...
on a perfect day.

178
00:15:42.151 --> 00:15:44.987
one could see clear
across the Sunset Sea.

179
00:15:45.947 --> 00:15:47.365
It must be quite something.

180
00:15:47.448 --> 00:15:50.618
Mmm. I don't have a Dragonpit.
of course. but...

181
00:15:50.701 --> 00:15:53.329
I do have the means
and resources to build one.

182
00:15:54.455 --> 00:15:56.457
Why would you need a Dragonpit?

183
00:15:57.041 --> 00:15:58.876
To house dragons. of course.

184
00:15:58.960 --> 00:16:00.962
I'd do anything for my queen...

185
00:16:02.004 --> 00:16:04.590
or... lady wife.

186
00:16:10.304 --> 00:16:11.556
Thank you for the wine.

187
00:16:26.112 --> 00:16:28.322
Is that what I am to you?

188
00:16:28.406 --> 00:16:31.033
A prize to proffer about
to the great houses?

189
00:16:35.788 --> 00:16:37.790
You're of age. Rhaenyra.

190
00:16:39.041 --> 00:16:40.793
And Jason Lannister
is an excellent match.

191
00:16:40.877 --> 00:16:42.461
He's arrogant and self-serious.

192
00:16:42.545 --> 00:16:44.755
I thought you might have that in common.

193
00:16:45.923 --> 00:16:47.258
Since you came of age.

194
00:16:47.341 --> 00:16:49.635
I've been slowly drowning
in a lake of parchment

195
00:16:49.719 --> 00:16:51.554
flung from every corner of the realm.

196
00:16:51.637 --> 00:16:53.472
Marriage proposals. all.

197
00:16:53.556 --> 00:16:56.601
And I have tried often
to discuss it with you.

198
00:16:56.684 --> 00:16:58.394
but you've refused me at every turn.

199
00:16:58.477 --> 00:17:00.313
That is because I do not
wish to get married.

200
00:17:00.396 --> 00:17:02.982
Even I do not exist above tradition
and duty. Rhaenyra!

201
00:17:03.065 --> 00:17:04.942
Excuse me. Your Grace.

202
00:17:13.201 --> 00:17:14.493
You must marry.

203
00:17:17.914 --> 00:17:19.332
- Yes?
- The royal huntsman

204
00:17:19.415 --> 00:17:20.666
have sent a report. Your Grace.

205
00:17:20.750 --> 00:17:23.669
There's been a sighting of a white hart.

206
00:17:25.171 --> 00:17:27.381
The stag is "The King of the Kingswood."
Your Grace.

207
00:17:27.465 --> 00:17:30.384
A regal portent
for Prince Aegon's name day.

208
00:17:52.615 --> 00:17:54.033
Princess.

209
00:18:00.623 --> 00:18:02.041
Princess. wait!

210
00:18:21.894 --> 00:18:23.104
Princess. slow down!

211
00:18:32.738 --> 00:18:33.823
Princess!

212
00:18:36.492 --> 00:18:37.493
No!

213
00:18:39.578 --> 00:18:42.081
Whoa. whoa. now!

214
00:18:50.298 --> 00:18:52.300
What happened back there?

215
00:18:53.426 --> 00:18:55.511
My father...

216
00:18:55.594 --> 00:18:58.431
trying to sell me off
to Jason Lannister.

217
00:19:00.766 --> 00:19:04.562
Was I named heir to the Iron Throne

218
00:19:04.645 --> 00:19:07.189
so that I might only
further raise the standing

219
00:19:07.273 --> 00:19:09.275
of a Lord of Casterly Rock?

220
00:19:12.737 --> 00:19:14.405
Do you want me to kill him?

221
00:19:20.036 --> 00:19:23.122
We should return to camp. Princess.

222
00:19:26.125 --> 00:19:27.752
It's a beautiful day.

223
00:19:28.627 --> 00:19:30.629
We should take in the Kingswood.

224
00:19:36.260 --> 00:19:38.929
Were you ever betrothed. Ser Criston?

225
00:19:39.013 --> 00:19:41.682
I had an adventurous youth
when my father

226
00:19:41.766 --> 00:19:44.393
served at Blackhaven. to be sure.

227
00:19:44.477 --> 00:19:47.313
But my station was never high enough
for a formal betrothal.

228
00:19:47.897 --> 00:19:50.107
Before I spoke my vows
as a knight of the Kingsguard.

229
00:19:50.191 --> 00:19:52.193
I could've married
a common-born girl had I wished.

230
00:19:52.276 --> 00:19:55.571
How lucky you are to have
a say in your own life.

231
00:19:55.654 --> 00:19:58.908
Many in the realm would gladly
trade positions with you. Princess.

232
00:20:00.701 --> 00:20:03.704
Only because none of them
has ever held my position.

233
00:20:04.747 --> 00:20:07.750
I may be the Princess of Dragonstone.
but I am toothless.

234
00:20:10.378 --> 00:20:11.587
One day...

235
00:20:12.505 --> 00:20:14.548
not so long ago.

236
00:20:14.632 --> 00:20:18.135
you held enough power to write my name
into the White Book.

237
00:20:18.219 --> 00:20:20.137
And when your father
named me to his Kingsguard.

238
00:20:20.221 --> 00:20:22.640
it was the highest honor
any Cole have ever known.

239
00:20:23.849 --> 00:20:25.851
All that I have. I owe to you.

240
00:20:27.937 --> 00:20:30.940
Now I'd hardly call that
toothless. Princess.

241
00:21:03.347 --> 00:21:05.307
- Your Grace.
- How far?

242
00:21:05.391 --> 00:21:08.060
Her droppings were found
half a league to the east.

243
00:21:10.771 --> 00:21:11.771
Oh.

244
00:21:12.606 --> 00:21:13.816
Still fresh.

245
00:21:13.899 --> 00:21:15.818
Between two and three hours.
Your Grace.

246
00:21:15.901 --> 00:21:17.653
My best scouts spied him.

247
00:21:17.736 --> 00:21:19.989
The beast is upward of 35 stone.

248
00:21:20.072 --> 00:21:22.450
And we now have his trail.

249
00:21:22.533 --> 00:21:25.703
- Aye.
- Before the dragons ruled over Westeros.

250
00:21:25.786 --> 00:21:28.456
the white hart was a symbol of royalty
in these lands.

251
00:21:30.040 --> 00:21:31.792
And on this day of all days.

252
00:21:32.835 --> 00:21:35.796
I've never been one
for signs and portents. Your Grace.

253
00:21:35.880 --> 00:21:39.091
but if the gods did wish
to show their favor...

254
00:22:21.217 --> 00:22:22.551
Your Grace...

255
00:22:25.554 --> 00:22:29.391
I had this forged in the Golden Gallery
in honor of Prince Aegon.

256
00:22:35.481 --> 00:22:36.481
Uh...

257
00:22:41.153 --> 00:22:42.238
It's quite a thing.

258
00:22:44.031 --> 00:22:45.241
I hope it might provide

259
00:22:45.324 --> 00:22:47.409
the killing stroke
against your white hart.

260
00:22:50.287 --> 00:22:52.289
The King of the Kingswood.

261
00:22:53.958 --> 00:22:56.961
It's as if the Seven themselves
have blessed this day.

262
00:22:57.044 --> 00:23:00.047
Thank you for your generosity.

263
00:23:02.883 --> 00:23:04.510
I would be honored

264
00:23:05.636 --> 00:23:08.639
to take the Princess Rhaenyra
to wife. Your Grace.

265
00:23:09.974 --> 00:23:11.559
What I offer you.

266
00:23:11.642 --> 00:23:14.937
The Crown and your daughter.
is strength.

267
00:23:17.648 --> 00:23:21.819
Do you think that House Targaryen
wants for strength?

268
00:23:22.278 --> 00:23:25.239
If someone offered you more dragons.
would you not take them?

269
00:23:25.906 --> 00:23:28.534
Do you have dragons to offer?

270
00:23:30.995 --> 00:23:33.372
Casterly Rock is a splendid seat.

271
00:23:33.455 --> 00:23:36.667
Rhaenyra may take her place there
by my side. without shame.

272
00:23:36.750 --> 00:23:39.753
and feel herself well-compensated
for her loss in station.

273
00:23:40.462 --> 00:23:42.464
What loss of station?

274
00:23:43.299 --> 00:23:46.510
If you were to name
young Aegon heir. Your Grace.

275
00:23:46.594 --> 00:23:48.804
And when would I be doing that?

276
00:23:50.180 --> 00:23:53.976
I had assumed...
As he's your firstborn son...

277
00:23:54.059 --> 00:23:56.979
- Many of us had assumed...
- Many of us. you say?

278
00:23:57.980 --> 00:24:00.566
Have your bannermen
questioned my choice of heir?

279
00:24:00.649 --> 00:24:01.859
Of course not. Your Grace.

280
00:24:01.942 --> 00:24:04.111
It is your sworn duty
to report rebellion

281
00:24:04.194 --> 00:24:06.363
- stirring in my kingdom.
- Rebellion?

282
00:24:06.447 --> 00:24:09.033
There's been nothing
of the sort. Your Grace.

283
00:24:09.116 --> 00:24:13.162
I did not decide to name
Rhaenyra my heir on a whim.

284
00:24:14.413 --> 00:24:18.167
All the lords of the kingdom
would do well to remember that.

285
00:24:20.878 --> 00:24:23.881
Thank you... for the gift.

286
00:24:27.092 --> 00:24:28.302
Your Grace.

287
00:24:32.931 --> 00:24:34.016
Wine.

288
00:24:46.987 --> 00:24:50.532
The huntsman has the trail. Your Grace.
and has sent out the hounds.

289
00:24:50.616 --> 00:24:52.910
It won't be long now
until the white hart is cornered.

290
00:24:52.993 --> 00:24:55.621
Your prize is within reach.

291
00:24:57.665 --> 00:25:00.668
What do you make
of Lord Jason's proposal?

292
00:25:01.251 --> 00:25:04.046
That man's pride has pride.

293
00:25:07.257 --> 00:25:10.678
You're not only Rhaenyra's father.
you're the King.

294
00:25:11.553 --> 00:25:13.389
She'll do as you command.

295
00:25:14.640 --> 00:25:18.060
It is not my wish to command her. Otto.

296
00:25:18.143 --> 00:25:20.145
I want her to be happy.

297
00:25:26.026 --> 00:25:29.029
There is another choice
beyond Casterly Rock.

298
00:25:30.239 --> 00:25:33.492
One. perhaps. you might be more
comfortable with.

299
00:25:33.575 --> 00:25:36.370
One... closer to home.

300
00:25:37.037 --> 00:25:39.164
Who do you have in mind?

301
00:25:42.459 --> 00:25:43.836
Prince Aegon.

302
00:25:53.011 --> 00:25:54.722
The boy just turned two. Otto.

303
00:25:54.805 --> 00:25:56.890
Yes. but it would cease

304
00:25:56.974 --> 00:25:59.476
the endless proposals
for Rhaenyra's hand.

305
00:26:01.311 --> 00:26:04.732
- Betroth them.
- I came here to hunt...

306
00:26:04.815 --> 00:26:08.819
not to be suffocated
by all this fucking politicking.

307
00:26:09.945 --> 00:26:11.947
Let us speak no more of it.

308
00:27:04.500 --> 00:27:07.795
We've sent out riders
to find Rhaenyra. Your Grace.

309
00:27:08.295 --> 00:27:11.173
Ser Criston went after her.
so the hope is that they are together.

310
00:27:11.256 --> 00:27:13.634
The girl is a heedless contrarian.

311
00:27:14.927 --> 00:27:17.596
If I instead forbade her
to wed a Lannister.

312
00:27:17.679 --> 00:27:20.891
she would've run off
with Lord Jason out of spite.

313
00:27:22.392 --> 00:27:25.020
A truly great Targaryen King I am.

314
00:27:26.021 --> 00:27:29.316
Powerless over mine own
daughter of seven-and-ten.

315
00:27:30.150 --> 00:27:32.820
King Jaehaerys ruled over
half a century of peace

316
00:27:32.903 --> 00:27:36.365
while his children drove him
to the edge of madness...

317
00:27:36.448 --> 00:27:38.659
his daughters. in particular.

318
00:27:38.742 --> 00:27:41.119
It is tradition. Your Grace.

319
00:27:48.043 --> 00:27:50.587
Do you wish to hear
my opinion on the matter?

320
00:27:55.050 --> 00:27:56.802
Should I guess?

321
00:27:58.929 --> 00:28:00.639
You believe that your son.

322
00:28:00.722 --> 00:28:03.225
Ser Harwin "Breakbones."

323
00:28:03.308 --> 00:28:06.520
the strongest knight
in the Seven Kingdoms.

324
00:28:06.603 --> 00:28:08.856
is the best match for Rhaenyra.

325
00:28:10.649 --> 00:28:12.734
You flatter me. Your Grace. but no.

326
00:28:13.777 --> 00:28:16.071
It would seem to me
the best match for Rhaenyra

327
00:28:16.154 --> 00:28:17.739
is the son of the Sea Snake.

328
00:28:17.823 --> 00:28:18.991
Ser Laenor.

329
00:28:20.158 --> 00:28:23.245
Some years ago. I counseled you
to take his sister to wife.

330
00:28:23.328 --> 00:28:25.330
My reasoning remains the same.

331
00:28:26.373 --> 00:28:29.001
Laenor is of pure Valyrian descent.

332
00:28:29.835 --> 00:28:32.713
He shares blood with your cousin.
the Princess Rhaenys.

333
00:28:33.338 --> 00:28:36.758
And he is the heir to the wealthiest
house in the realm.

334
00:28:37.718 --> 00:28:39.136
The breach between your houses

335
00:28:39.219 --> 00:28:40.888
has not narrowed
since I last spoke of it.

336
00:28:40.971 --> 00:28:43.181
It would do much to assuage Lord Corlys

337
00:28:43.265 --> 00:28:46.101
of any slights real... or imagined.

338
00:28:51.940 --> 00:28:54.234
We must pray. of course.
that Laenor survives

339
00:28:54.318 --> 00:28:55.819
the fighting in the Stepstones.

340
00:29:34.858 --> 00:29:37.861
Princess. I must make a final plea
that we return to the camp.

341
00:29:39.237 --> 00:29:41.239
I rather prefer it here.

342
00:29:43.158 --> 00:29:46.370
His Grace is certain to be worried
by your absence.

343
00:29:46.453 --> 00:29:50.457
His Grace can worry
himself to death if he so likes.

344
00:30:00.759 --> 00:30:02.260
Tell me something. Ser Criston.

345
00:30:04.054 --> 00:30:07.057
Do you think the realm will
ever accept me as their Queen?

346
00:30:14.731 --> 00:30:17.359
They'll have no choice but to. Princess.

347
00:32:13.391 --> 00:32:15.393
Is everything all right. Your Grace?

348
00:32:19.189 --> 00:32:20.565
You know. I...

349
00:32:21.566 --> 00:32:25.779
I named her to protect
the realm from Daemon.

350
00:32:28.406 --> 00:32:30.242
She was my only child.

351
00:32:31.743 --> 00:32:33.745
"The Realm's Delight."

352
00:32:34.663 --> 00:32:36.665
I named her out of love

353
00:32:37.791 --> 00:32:39.960
because I no longer believed...

354
00:32:41.503 --> 00:32:43.130
Believed what. my love?

355
00:32:51.555 --> 00:32:54.558
Many in my line have been dragonriders.

356
00:32:56.643 --> 00:32:59.020
Very few among us have been dreamers.

357
00:33:03.525 --> 00:33:06.027
What is the power of a dragon...

358
00:33:06.111 --> 00:33:08.071
next to the power of prophecy?

359
00:33:08.155 --> 00:33:09.614
The hour is too late. husband.

360
00:33:09.698 --> 00:33:11.783
When Rhaenyra was a child...

361
00:33:12.784 --> 00:33:14.786
I saw it in a dream...

362
00:33:15.954 --> 00:33:18.373
as vivid as these flames.
I saw it.

363
00:33:20.125 --> 00:33:23.712
A male babe born to me...

364
00:33:23.795 --> 00:33:25.797
wearing the Conqueror's crown.

365
00:33:28.133 --> 00:33:30.594
And I so wanted it to be true.

366
00:33:30.677 --> 00:33:32.888
to be a dreamer myself.

367
00:33:35.098 --> 00:33:38.101
I sought that vision again.
night after night...

368
00:33:39.477 --> 00:33:41.479
but it never came again.

369
00:33:43.064 --> 00:33:46.151
I poured all my thought
and will into it.

370
00:33:48.653 --> 00:33:51.281
And my obsession
killed Rhaenyra's mother.

371
00:33:51.364 --> 00:33:52.824
Viserys.

372
00:33:53.867 --> 00:33:58.872
I thought Rhaenyra was the
way out of my abyss of grief and regret.

373
00:34:00.832 --> 00:34:03.293
And naming her heir
would begin to set things right.

374
00:34:03.376 --> 00:34:06.379
- Oh. it did.
- I never imagined I would remarry...

375
00:34:07.297 --> 00:34:08.924
that I would have a son.

376
00:34:13.929 --> 00:34:15.931
What if I was wrong?

377
00:35:17.701 --> 00:35:18.910
Left.

378
00:35:27.294 --> 00:35:29.546
He may not be white. Your Grace.

379
00:35:29.629 --> 00:35:30.755
But he's a big lad.

380
00:35:37.762 --> 00:35:41.141
Your Grace... for the kill.

381
00:36:06.791 --> 00:36:08.418
Right here. Your Grace.

382
00:36:38.823 --> 00:36:41.826
One more time. Your Grace.
A little bit to your left.

383
00:38:13.293 --> 00:38:14.711
No.

384
00:39:37.669 --> 00:39:38.962
Come. sweet Prince.

385
00:39:39.045 --> 00:39:41.214
Let's give Her Grace some peace.

386
00:39:56.145 --> 00:39:57.981
Did you enjoy the hunt. Your Grace?

387
00:39:59.148 --> 00:40:02.610
- Well enough.
- How fared my grandson?

388
00:40:03.736 --> 00:40:06.322
The ladies Lannister and Redwyne
were quite taken with him.

389
00:40:06.406 --> 00:40:08.408
As they should be.

390
00:40:09.325 --> 00:40:11.327
He's the future of the realm.

391
00:40:12.912 --> 00:40:15.915
You yourself witnessed
the scale of the celebration.

392
00:40:15.999 --> 00:40:18.251
how it's united the men.

393
00:40:18.334 --> 00:40:19.752
When you bore the King a son.

394
00:40:19.836 --> 00:40:23.047
you ended 15 years
of uncertainty and doubt.

395
00:40:24.048 --> 00:40:25.466
Aegon. like his namesake.

396
00:40:25.550 --> 00:40:27.969
was born to rule the Seven Kingdoms.

397
00:40:28.886 --> 00:40:32.890
If Viserys were to name him heir.
the realm would fete him for it.

398
00:40:38.479 --> 00:40:40.106
And does this not please you?

399
00:40:40.565 --> 00:40:44.193
- Do you not want your son to be King?
- And what mother wouldn't?

400
00:40:45.320 --> 00:40:47.280
You mustn't ignore
the certain truth

401
00:40:47.363 --> 00:40:50.491
that if Rhaenyra were to step over Aegon
to ascend the throne.

402
00:40:50.575 --> 00:40:52.910
the realm would tear itself apart.

403
00:40:54.871 --> 00:40:58.082
They all swore obeisance to her.
our house among them.

404
00:40:58.166 --> 00:41:00.168
That was before Aegon.

405
00:41:01.502 --> 00:41:02.920
Rhaenyra will be a good queen.

406
00:41:03.004 --> 00:41:07.425
It wouldn't matter if she were
Jaehaerys himself born again.

407
00:41:09.385 --> 00:41:12.305
- Rhaenyra is a woman.
- What of my son?

408
00:41:12.388 --> 00:41:15.308
Would you have me raise a man
to steal his own sister's birthright?

409
00:41:15.391 --> 00:41:18.311
It is Aegon that's being robbed.

410
00:41:18.394 --> 00:41:20.355
He's the firstborn son of the King.

411
00:41:20.438 --> 00:41:22.523
To deny that he is heir to the throne

412
00:41:22.607 --> 00:41:24.984
is to assail the laws of gods and men.

413
00:41:27.195 --> 00:41:31.157
The road ahead is uncertain.
but the end is clear.

414
00:41:31.240 --> 00:41:33.242
Aegon will be king.

415
00:41:34.994 --> 00:41:37.622
You must guide Viserys towards reason.

416
00:41:40.416 --> 00:41:42.418
<i>He'll never find it on his own.</i>

417
00:41:50.343 --> 00:41:51.928
How are you feeling. husband?

418
00:41:52.011 --> 00:41:54.972
The gods have punished me
for my indulgences.

419
00:41:55.056 --> 00:41:57.225
At least the wine was good.

420
00:41:57.308 --> 00:41:58.868
Too good.

421
00:42:10.947 --> 00:42:13.032
I was hoping we might discuss something.

422
00:42:16.160 --> 00:42:17.370
Rhaenyra?

423
00:42:21.457 --> 00:42:23.876
I do not think she enjoyed
Jason Lannister's company.

424
00:42:25.211 --> 00:42:27.422
She is cross.

425
00:42:27.505 --> 00:42:29.382
I warned you that she would be.

426
00:42:29.465 --> 00:42:31.426
Rhaenyra has come of age.

427
00:42:31.509 --> 00:42:34.345
She must needs marry a high lord
who will honor her. defend her.

428
00:42:34.429 --> 00:42:36.180
and serve her as king consort.

429
00:42:36.889 --> 00:42:39.684
Her wishes in this matter
are irrelevant.

430
00:42:39.767 --> 00:42:42.770
I do believe that Rhaenyra
will marry. Your Grace.

431
00:42:43.521 --> 00:42:46.566
But she must believe
it is her choice to do so.

432
00:42:55.241 --> 00:42:57.660
- What's this?
- A letter...

433
00:42:59.704 --> 00:43:01.706
...from Vaemond Velaryon.

434
00:43:02.165 --> 00:43:04.792
- The Sea Snake's brother?
- Yeah.

435
00:43:05.626 --> 00:43:08.045
He's fighting in the Stepstones.

436
00:43:08.129 --> 00:43:09.756
with all the rest of them.

437
00:43:15.052 --> 00:43:16.137
May I?

438
00:43:27.190 --> 00:43:29.817
Lord Corlys and Prince Daemon
are losing their war.

439
00:43:30.443 --> 00:43:32.653
Badly. by all accounts.

440
00:43:33.404 --> 00:43:35.281
This is a plea for aid.

441
00:43:37.825 --> 00:43:39.827
Then why not send it?

442
00:43:39.911 --> 00:43:42.997
Because it is a war
started by two malcontents.

443
00:43:43.080 --> 00:43:45.291
unhappy with decisions I made.

444
00:43:46.751 --> 00:43:49.921
If I now provide
Daemon and Corlys succor.

445
00:43:50.004 --> 00:43:51.464
what will that say of their King?

446
00:43:51.547 --> 00:43:54.258
Perhaps. that he is a good man who
loves his brother.

447
00:43:54.342 --> 00:43:57.637
Well. if you truly
believe that. my dear...

448
00:43:57.720 --> 00:43:59.931
then you possess a generous spirit.

449
00:44:01.432 --> 00:44:03.768
What do you believe. Viserys?

450
00:44:07.104 --> 00:44:09.273
That I am forever doomed
to anger one person

451
00:44:09.357 --> 00:44:10.983
in the pleasing of another.

452
00:44:11.692 --> 00:44:13.694
Then I pose
a simpler question.

453
00:44:14.779 --> 00:44:17.824
Is it better for the realm
if the Crabfeeder thrives.

454
00:44:17.907 --> 00:44:19.534
or is vanquished?

455
00:44:26.290 --> 00:44:28.292
Make haste to Dwarfstone.
Ser Addam.

456
00:44:28.376 --> 00:44:30.711
Hand-deliver this
to Prince Daemon yourself.

457
00:44:30.795 --> 00:44:32.380
At once. Your Grace.

458
00:44:40.888 --> 00:44:44.308
- Dwarfstone?
- I'm sending word to Daemon.

459
00:44:44.392 --> 00:44:46.811
Aid is sailing to the Stepstones.

460
00:44:47.813 --> 00:44:51.649
- Did he make call for help?
- He would sooner die.

461
00:44:51.732 --> 00:44:53.943
But his king does not mean
to allow that.

462
00:44:58.573 --> 00:45:00.783
Do you not think my decision correct?

463
00:45:00.867 --> 00:45:03.369
It is no consequence to what I think...

464
00:45:03.452 --> 00:45:05.329
as I'm often reminded.

465
00:45:07.832 --> 00:45:10.459
Daemon is thorn enough in my flesh.

466
00:45:11.210 --> 00:45:13.087
Will you insist on taking after him?

467
00:45:14.505 --> 00:45:16.173
Must everything be a battle?

468
00:45:16.257 --> 00:45:19.552
If you refer to your attempt
to marry me off to Casterly Rock...

469
00:45:21.178 --> 00:45:22.597
I am sorry. Rhaenyra.

470
00:45:23.806 --> 00:45:27.351
I was trying to help you.
Will you not be helped?

471
00:45:28.561 --> 00:45:31.939
Why must every effort
on your behalf be resisted

472
00:45:32.023 --> 00:45:34.942
- as if to the death?
- Because you mean to replace me...

473
00:45:35.860 --> 00:45:38.154
with Alicent Hightower's son.

474
00:45:38.237 --> 00:45:40.698
the boy you always wanted.

475
00:45:41.449 --> 00:45:42.992
You have him in hands now.

476
00:45:43.075 --> 00:45:45.620
You have no further use for me.

477
00:45:45.703 --> 00:45:47.997
You might as well peddle me
for what you can.

478
00:45:48.080 --> 00:45:51.626
A mountain stronghold
or a fleet of ships.

479
00:45:51.709 --> 00:45:53.753
You have misjudged me. Rhaenyra.

480
00:45:53.836 --> 00:45:55.630
All know it.

481
00:45:55.713 --> 00:45:57.798
Jason Lannister knows it.

482
00:45:57.882 --> 00:45:59.383
You said it yourself.

483
00:45:59.467 --> 00:46:02.303
the lords of the realm
gather like vultures to a carcass.

484
00:46:02.386 --> 00:46:04.388
hoping to feast on my bones.

485
00:46:06.933 --> 00:46:11.062
It is true that as rulers
we must marry for advantage

486
00:46:11.145 --> 00:46:14.231
to forge alliances
and bolster our strength.

487
00:46:14.315 --> 00:46:16.776
You have always understood this.

488
00:46:17.443 --> 00:46:19.862
I myself was promised
to your mother when I was...

489
00:46:19.946 --> 00:46:21.864
Ten-and-seven years of age.

490
00:46:21.948 --> 00:46:23.783
The Vale had an army to rival the North.

491
00:46:23.866 --> 00:46:26.410
I've heard that story
since I've had ears to.

492
00:46:27.620 --> 00:46:29.622
I loved her.

493
00:46:30.247 --> 00:46:31.666
She made a man of me.

494
00:46:35.252 --> 00:46:37.630
I do not seek to replace you. child.

495
00:46:39.256 --> 00:46:41.509
You've been much alone
these last few years.

496
00:46:41.592 --> 00:46:43.594
Alone and angry.

497
00:46:45.096 --> 00:46:46.806
I will not live forever.

498
00:46:46.889 --> 00:46:48.891
I wish to see you contented.

499
00:46:48.975 --> 00:46:50.476
happy even.

500
00:46:50.559 --> 00:46:51.852
You think a man will do it?

501
00:46:51.936 --> 00:46:53.938
- A family.
- I had a family.

502
00:46:54.021 --> 00:46:55.564
What would you have me do?

503
00:46:55.648 --> 00:46:58.651
If it was for advantage.
you would've wed Laena Velaryon!

504
00:47:03.572 --> 00:47:05.199
That is true enough.

505
00:47:07.868 --> 00:47:09.996
You must marry.

506
00:47:10.705 --> 00:47:13.332
strengthen your own claim.

507
00:47:13.416 --> 00:47:15.626
shore up your succession.

508
00:47:15.710 --> 00:47:17.128
multiply.

509
00:47:18.546 --> 00:47:20.256
As to your match...

510
00:47:21.966 --> 00:47:23.342
make it yourself.

511
00:47:24.427 --> 00:47:26.178
Search him out.

512
00:47:26.262 --> 00:47:29.849
Find one that pleases you. as I did.

513
00:47:45.406 --> 00:47:46.615
Rhaenyra...

514
00:47:52.621 --> 00:47:55.374
I did waver at one time.

515
00:47:57.084 --> 00:48:00.504
But I swear to you now.
on your mother's memory.

516
00:48:01.589 --> 00:48:03.090
you will not be supplanted.

517
00:48:47.134 --> 00:48:50.387
<i>We have 16. perhaps 18.
seaworthy ships.</i>

518
00:48:50.471 --> 00:48:52.723
<i>Seven hundred foot. some 60 knights.</i>

519
00:48:52.807 --> 00:48:56.560
<i>Our food quickly dwindles.
save for what we can fish from the sea.</i>

520
00:48:56.644 --> 00:48:57.978
<i>I would say we have a fortnight.</i>

521
00:48:58.062 --> 00:49:00.773
<i>mayhaps a bit longer
with strict rationing.</i>

522
00:49:00.856 --> 00:49:02.858
<i>I've made call for Driftmark
to send more ships.</i>

523
00:49:02.942 --> 00:49:05.528
<i>but they will be weeks away.</i>

524
00:49:05.611 --> 00:49:08.114
<i>We are faltering
and the Triarchy knows it.</i>

525
00:49:08.197 --> 00:49:11.784
<i>We must press the attack.
continue sending the dragons.</i>

526
00:49:11.867 --> 00:49:13.160
It's pointless. Father.

527
00:49:14.203 --> 00:49:16.997
The Crabfeeder has
created a chokepoint here.

528
00:49:17.081 --> 00:49:18.749
beyond these dunes.

529
00:49:19.250 --> 00:49:20.626
Archers hold the high positions.

530
00:49:20.709 --> 00:49:22.378
foot soldiers hold the ground.

531
00:49:22.461 --> 00:49:24.630
We've strafed them on
dragonback again and again.

532
00:49:24.713 --> 00:49:27.007
but they just retreat within the caves.

533
00:49:27.091 --> 00:49:30.845
Dragons can circle Bloodstone
until they fall out of the sky.

534
00:49:30.928 --> 00:49:33.973
The Crabfeeder and his men
have no reason to leave those caves.

535
00:49:34.431 --> 00:49:35.891
We must give them one.

536
00:49:35.975 --> 00:49:38.853
an offering of flesh to bait the crab.

537
00:49:38.936 --> 00:49:40.521
Who?

538
00:49:40.604 --> 00:49:42.439
Dragon returning!

539
00:49:49.697 --> 00:49:51.198
Yes. Who?

540
00:49:51.282 --> 00:49:53.701
Which man here
will happily go to his death?

541
00:49:53.784 --> 00:49:55.846
Show me the knight
who will march into that hell pit.

542
00:49:55.870 --> 00:49:57.580
nephew. and I will show you a madman.

543
00:49:57.663 --> 00:50:00.499
- Daemon.
- Daemon is why we are losing!

544
00:50:00.583 --> 00:50:03.002
He at least
is fighting this war.

545
00:50:03.085 --> 00:50:05.754
What role have you played
in his council. Uncle.

546
00:50:05.838 --> 00:50:07.649
- other than Master of Complaints?
- Enough. Laenor.

547
00:50:07.673 --> 00:50:10.676
If King's Landing
will not support Daemon.

548
00:50:10.759 --> 00:50:12.428
why should any of us?

549
00:50:18.642 --> 00:50:22.646
Blood or no. Vaemond.
I will not have you stoke mutiny.

550
00:50:44.210 --> 00:50:46.629
If you do not seize control
of this war. my lord.

551
00:50:46.712 --> 00:50:49.131
the crabs will soon dine on all of us.

552
00:51:05.564 --> 00:51:06.941
Prince Daemon.

553
00:51:07.024 --> 00:51:09.818
I bring word from His Grace.
Viserys Targaryen.

554
00:51:09.902 --> 00:51:11.654
first of his name. King of the Andals.

555
00:51:11.737 --> 00:51:13.614
the Rhoynar. and the First Men.

556
00:51:13.697 --> 00:51:16.700
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms.
and Protector of the Realm.

557
00:51:59.493 --> 00:52:03.080
That's enough! Stop!

558
00:52:18.304 --> 00:52:19.430
<i>Brother...</i>

559
00:52:20.347 --> 00:52:24.810
<i>I have ordered 10 ships and 2.000 men
to set sail from King's Landing</i>

560
00:52:24.893 --> 00:52:27.313
<i>to join the effort in the Stepstones.</i>

561
00:52:28.731 --> 00:52:32.192
<i>Though time and circumstance
have seen us estranged.</i>

562
00:52:32.276 --> 00:52:36.905
<i>know that it is not my desire to see you
fail in your cause.</i>

563
00:52:36.989 --> 00:52:39.450
<i>It is instead my hope
that this aid will deliver</i>

564
00:52:39.533 --> 00:52:42.328
<i>the victory that has thus far evaded us.</i>

565
00:52:44.580 --> 00:52:48.208
<i>I shall pray nightly to
the gods for your safe return.</i>

566
00:54:41.738 --> 00:54:42.948
Nock.

567
00:55:07.389 --> 00:55:08.640
Draw.

568
00:55:48.514 --> 00:55:49.515
Loose!

569
00:55:58.023 --> 00:55:59.233
Loose!

570
00:56:14.915 --> 00:56:15.916
Loose!

571
00:56:34.726 --> 00:56:36.144
Loose!

572
00:59:17.597 --> 00:59:19.099
<i>Dracarys!</i>

573
00:59:32.612 --> 00:59:34.406
Nock!

574
00:59:35.073 --> 00:59:36.700
Dragon!

575
01:00:37.969 --> 01:00:40.013
Whoo!

576
01:00:56.822 --> 01:00:57.989
<i>Dracarys!</i>

576
01:00:58.305 --> 01:01:58.494
